---
description: Rules for all React/TypeScript frontend code
globs: "frontend/src/**/*.ts, frontend/src/**/*.tsx"
alwaysApply: false
---

## TypeScript

- Strict mode — no `any`, no `// @ts-ignore`
- Explicit return types on all functions and hooks
- Use `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions/aliases

## API and data fetching

- All REST calls via `src/services/api.ts` — never raw `fetch`
- All WebSocket connections via `src/services/ws.ts`
- Use React Query (`useQuery`, `useMutation`) for all server state
- Never `useEffect` + `fetch` — this is an anti-pattern

## Permissions

- Use `useStudioAccess()` for all permission checks
- Unauthorised elements must be absent from DOM — not hidden with CSS:

  ```tsx
  // CORRECT
  {canEdit && <EditButton />}
  // WRONG
  <EditButton className={canEdit ? '' : 'hidden'} />
  ```

## Streaming

- Use `useStream()` hook for all SSE LLM responses
- Never manage `EventSource` manually in components

## Component rules

- One component per file
- Co-locate test: `Button.tsx` + `Button.test.tsx`
- No inline styles — Tailwind only
- No barrel `index.ts` that re-exports everything
